{{wiktionary|gerontophilia}}
The term '''gerontophilia''' refers to the [[sexual preference]] for the [[elderly]]. The word derives from [[Greek language|Greek]]: geron, meaning "old man" and philie, meaning "love". A synonym is '''graeophilia'''.<ref>{{Cite journal | last1 = Kaul | first1 = A. | last2 = Duffy | first2 = S. | year = 1991 | title = Gerontophilia: A case report | url = | journal = Medicine, Science and the Law | volume = 31 | issue = | pages = 110–114 }}</ref>
A person who has a sexual preference for the elderly is a '''[[gerontophile]]''' or '''[[graeophile]]'''.
Specialised terms are '''[[alphamegamia]]''' for the attraction to an older man and '''[[wikt:anililagnia|anililagnia]]''' for the attraction to an older woman.{{Citation needed|date=November 2009}}
